es<ref>{{cite web| |url= http://www.adclassix.com/ads/80yamaha125atv.htm |title=1980 Yamaha YT125G Tri-Moto Advertisement |website=adclassix.com||accessdate=2020-04-16 |url-status=live}}</ref>.\n\n\nYamaha followed the YT125 with the introduction of the YT175 in 1982\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ style=\"text-align: left;\" |\n|-\n!  scope=\"col\" |{{Infobox Motorcycle\n|name             = Yamaha YT125G Tri-Moto\n|manufacturer     = [[Yamaha]]\n|parent_company   = \n|production       = 1980-1985\n|assembly         =\n|predecessor      = \n|successor        = \n|class            = [[All-terrain vehicle|Recreation ATC]]\n|engine           = {{Convert|123|cc|abbr=on}} [[Radiator (engine cooling)|air-cooled]] [[two-stroke]] [[Single-cylinder engine|single]]\n|bore_stroke      = 56 x 50\n|compression      = 6.4:1\n|top_speed        = <30 Mph \n|power            = \n|torque           = 7.2 ft-lbs@5000rpm\n|ignition         = CDI \n|transmission     = Auto-clutch<br>5-speed<br>Chain Final Drive\n|frame            = Steel  \n|suspension       = None\n|brakes           = Front: None<br>Rear: Drum\n|tires            = 22 x 11 x 8\n|wheelbase        = 44.1 \n|length           = 69.7 \n|width            = 39.2\n|height           = \n|seat_height      = 27.2 \n|dry_weight       = 243\n| wet_weight       = \n| fuel_capacity    = 1.8gal\n| oil_capacity     = \n| fuel_consumption = \n| turning_radius   = \n| range            = \n| related          = $1049 MSRP\n| sp               =\n| footnotes        = <ref>{{cite web| |url= http://www.3wheelerworld.com/oldsite/1980yamahaspecpage.shtml |title=Yamaha YT125G Tri-Moto Specs |website=3wheelerworld.com||accessdate=2020-04-15 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n!! scope=\"col\" | {{Infobox Motorcycle\n|name             = Yamaha YT175J Tri-Moto\n|manufacturer     = [[Yamaha]]\n|parent_company   = \n|production       = 1982-1983\n|assembly         =\n|predecessor      = \n|successor        = \n|class            = [[All-terrain vehicle|Recreatio